For that reason, some White House officials say they think a Human Rights Campaign endorsement of D'Amato will be almost meaningless among gay voters.
Some New York advocates of civil rights for gay people have flooded the organization with phone calls, e-mail messages and letters.
"I don't think anybody will vote for Al D'Amato because of an HRC endorsement," said a White House aide who spoke on the condition of anonymity.
Human Rights Campaign officials also say their standing policy is to support friendly incumbents, even when their challengers have better voting records on gay issues.